<TITLE> HC asks govt to explain Hannan Shah cases </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 28 (bdnews24.com) -- The High Court Monday asked the government to explain why BNP leader ASM Hannan Shah and son Shah Rezaul Hannan would not be granted bail in extortion and land grabbing cases. Police arrested Hannan Shah and Shah Rezaul Hannan at Mohakhali DOHS home on May 14 on charges of land grab. The bench of Justice Md Abdul Matin and Justice Md Abdul Hye issued the order. On May 19, bus-owner Noman filed a case against Hannan and Rezaul with Kapasia Police Station for extorting Tk 1 lakh. According to case details, Rezaul took the money in the presence of Hannan from Noman for attaching his buses with Bhawal Paribahan, a syndicated bus service provider. On May 20, fisherman Haripada Barman filed another case with the same police station against the duo for occupying a water body. The government has to explain to court why the proceedings of two other extortion casesagainst Hannan and Rezaulwould not be scrapped. Kapasia Awami League general secretary Ruhul Amin filed the extortion case against the duo for extorting Tk 1 lakh. The case against Rezaul alone was filed on May 12. bdnew
